(14, 'Insurance', '1742278394_png-clipart-vehicle-insurance-health-insurance-insurance-agent-work-safety-and-health-day-text-service-thumbnail-removebg-preview.png', '<p>Insurance is a contract where an insurer (like an insurance company) agrees to compensate the insured (the policyholder) for financial losses due to specific events, in exchange for regular payments called premiums</p>', 1),
(15, 'Real Estate', '1742278615_3847365beb7da39d34684ae14e4b7bf5-removebg-preview.png', '<p>Real estate is defined as&nbsp;<strong>the land and any permanent structures, like a home, or improvements attached to the land, whether natural or man-made</strong>. Real estate is a form of real property.</p>', 1),
(16, 'Software', '1742278821_ui-ux-designers-isometric-composition-with-small-people-creating-custom-design-web-site-3d-vector-illustration_1284-68939-removebg-preview.png', '<p>Software is&nbsp;a collection of instructions, data, or computer programs that instruct a computer to perform specific tasks, and it is the opposite of hardware, which refers to the physical components of a computer.&nbsp;</p>', 1),
(17, 'Solar power', '1742279210_czNmcy1wcml2YXRlL3Jhd3BpeGVsX2ltYWdlcy93ZWJzaXRlX2NvbnRlbnQvcm01MTktbS0wMV8xLWwxazFqajl6LmpwZw-removebg-preview.png', '<p>Solar power works by&nbsp;<strong>converting energy from the sun into power</strong>. There are two forms of energy generated from the sun for our use &ndash; electricity and heat. Both are generated through the use of solar panels, which range in size from residential rooftops to &#39;solar farms&#39; stretching over acres of rural land</p>', 1),
