(417, 9, 76, 'service', 'New York, USA', '<p>New York, USA, is one of the most iconic cities in the world, known for its towering skyscrapers, cultural diversity, and vibrant energy. Nicknamed &quot;The Big Apple,&quot; it is home to famous landmarks such as Times Square, Central Park, the Statue of Liberty, and the Empire State Building. As a global financial hub, Wall Street and the New York Stock Exchange play a crucial role in the world&#39;s economy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The city is a melting pot of cultures, with people from all over the world bringing their traditions, cuisine, and languages. Broadway in Manhattan is the heart of American theater, offering world-class performances. Museums like the Metropolitan Museum of Art and the Museum of Modern Art (MoMA) attract millions of visitors each year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New York is also known for its culinary scene, featuring everything from Michelin-starred restaurants to classic street foods like hot dogs and pretzels. The city never sleeps, with 24/7 entertainment, shopping, and nightlife.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743401432_usa.jpg', 1, NULL, 0),
(418, 9, 76, 'service', 'Paris, France', '<p>Paris, France, is one of the most beautiful and culturally rich cities in the world, known as the &quot;City of Light&quot; and a global center for art, fashion, and history. The Eiffel Tower, an iconic symbol of France, attracts millions of visitors each year, offering breathtaking views of the city. The Louvre Museum, home to the Mona Lisa and countless masterpieces, is the world&rsquo;s most-visited museum.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paris is also famous for its historic architecture, from the stunning Notre-Dame Cathedral to the grand Champs-&Eacute;lys&eacute;es leading to the Arc de Triomphe. The city&rsquo;s romantic atmosphere, charming caf&eacute;s, and picturesque streets make it a dream destination for travelers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a fashion capital, Paris hosts major events like Paris Fashion Week, showcasing top designers and luxury brands. French cuisine is another highlight, with famous dishes such as croissants, escargots, and coq au vin, as well as world-renowned pastries and fine wines.</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743401586_paris.jpg', 1, NULL, 0),
(419, 9, 76, 'service', 'Dubai, Emirates', '<p>Dubai, United Arab Emirates, is a global hub of luxury, innovation, and modern architecture. Known for its futuristic skyline, the city is home to the Burj Khalifa, the world&rsquo;s tallest building, offering breathtaking views from its observation deck. The Palm Jumeirah, a man-made island shaped like a palm tree, showcases Dubai&rsquo;s ambition and engineering excellence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dubai is famous for its extravagant shopping malls, including The Dubai Mall, which features an indoor aquarium and an ice rink. The city&rsquo;s traditional markets, or souks, such as the Gold Souk and Spice Souk, provide a glimpse into its rich cultural heritage. The Dubai Fountain, with its mesmerizing water and light shows, is a must-see attraction near the Burj Khalifa.</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743401686_dubai.jpg', 1, NULL, 0),
(420, 9, 76, 'service', 'Rome, Italty', '<p>Rome, Italy, is one of the most historic and culturally rich cities in the world, often referred to as the &quot;Eternal City.&quot; As the capital of Italy, it is a treasure trove of ancient ruins, Renaissance art, and religious landmarks. The iconic <strong>Colosseum</strong>, a symbol of Roman engineering, once hosted gladiator battles and remains a top tourist attraction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <strong>Vatican City</strong>, an independent city-state within Rome, is home to <strong>St. Peter&rsquo;s Basilica</strong>, the <strong>Sistine Chapel</strong> with Michelangelo&rsquo;s masterpiece, and the Pope. The <strong>Pantheon</strong>, with its grand dome, and the <strong>Roman Forum</strong>, once the heart of ancient Rome, showcase the city&#39;s rich past</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743401826_italy.jpg', 1, NULL, 0),
