(422, 9, 77, 'about', 'Deals & Discounts – Save More on Every Purchase!', '<p>Everyone loves a great deal, and with exclusive <strong>deals and discounts</strong>, you can save big on your favorite products and services. Whether you&rsquo;re shopping for fashion, electronics, travel, or dining, special offers make every purchase more rewarding. From <strong>seasonal sales</strong> to <strong>limited-time promotions</strong>, there&rsquo;s always an opportunity to grab the best bargains.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many brands offer <strong>coupon codes, cashback rewards, and buy-one-get-one (BOGO) deals</strong>, helping you stretch your budget while enjoying premium products. Online shoppers can take advantage of <strong>flash sales, festive discounts, and loyalty programs</strong> to get the best prices on top brands. Whether you&#39;re planning a holiday, upgrading your gadgets, or revamping your wardrobe, smart shopping can lead to huge savings.</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743402912_blog-image-6-600x480.jpg', 1, NULL, 0),
(423, 9, 77, 'service', 'Space Needle – Seattle’s Iconic Landmark', '<p>The <strong>Space Needle</strong> is one of the most recognizable landmarks in the United States, standing tall in <strong>Seattle, Washington</strong>. Built for the <strong>1962 World&rsquo;s Fair</strong>, this futuristic tower is a symbol of innovation and progress. With a height of <strong>605 feet (184 meters)</strong>, it offers breathtaking panoramic views of the <strong>Seattle skyline, Mount Rainier, Elliott Bay, and the Olympic Mountains</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <strong>observation deck</strong>, located at <strong>520 feet</strong>, provides a 360-degree view of the city. Visitors can also experience <strong>The Loupe</strong>, the world&#39;s first and only <strong>rotating glass floor</strong>, adding an exciting perspective of the city below. The Space Needle recently underwent a multimillion-dollar renovation, enhancing its glass walls and floors for an even more thrilling experience.</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743403166_client-6.png', 1, NULL, 0),
(424, 9, 77, 'service', 'Eiffel Tower – The Icon of Paris', '<p>The <strong>Eiffel Tower</strong> is one of the most famous landmarks in the world, symbolizing <strong>Paris, France</strong>. Built in <strong>1889</strong> for the <strong>Exposition Universelle</strong> (World&rsquo;s Fair), it was designed by <strong>Gustave Eiffel</strong> and originally met with mixed reactions. Today, it stands as a masterpiece of engineering and an enduring symbol of romance and elegance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rising <strong>330 meters (1,083 feet)</strong> tall, the Eiffel Tower offers breathtaking <strong>panoramic views of Paris</strong> from its three observation decks. Visitors can reach the top via elevators or take the stairs for a more adventurous climb. At night, the tower dazzles with its <strong>golden lights and hourly sparkle</strong>, making it one of the most photographed structures in the world.</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743403250_client-33.png', 1, NULL, 0),
(425, 9, 77, 'service', 'Tower Bridge – London’s Iconic Landmark', '<p>The <strong>Tower Bridge</strong> is one of the most famous and recognizable bridges in the world, located in <strong>London, England</strong>. Completed in <strong>1894</strong>, this stunning <strong>bascule and suspension bridge</strong> spans the <strong>River Thames</strong>, connecting the boroughs of Tower Hamlets and Southwark. Often mistaken for London Bridge, Tower Bridge is known for its <strong>Victorian Gothic architecture</strong> and <strong>iconic twin towers</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the bridge&rsquo;s most fascinating features is its <strong>bascule mechanism</strong>, allowing it to lift for passing ships. The bridge opens approximately <strong>800 times a year</strong>, providing a spectacular sight for visitors. The <strong>high-level glass walkway</strong>, located <strong>42 meters (138 feet) above the river</strong>, offers breathtaking panoramic views of London&rsquo;s skyline, including landmarks like the <strong>Tower of London, The Shard, and St. Paul&rsquo;s Cathedral</strong>.</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743403323_client-22.png', 1, NULL, 0),
