(464, 10, 84, 'about', 'About Our Treatments', '<p>At our facility, we offer <strong>advanced, patient-centered treatments</strong> designed to promote health, wellness, and recovery. Our expert medical team specializes in a wide range of services, ensuring personalized care for every patient.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Our Treatment Specialties:</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>✔ <strong>General Medicine</strong> &ndash; Diagnosis and management of common illnesses.<br />\r\n✔ <strong>Pediatrics</strong> &ndash; Specialized care for infants, children, and adolescents.<br />\r\n✔ <strong>Dental Care</strong> &ndash; Including <strong>cosmetic dentistry, pediatric dentistry, and dental implants</strong>.<br />\r\n✔ <strong>Neurology</strong> &ndash; Treatment for brain and nervous system disorders.<br />\r\n✔ <strong>Orthopedics</strong> &ndash; Expert care for bones, joints, and muscles.<br />\r\n✔ <strong>Cosmetic &amp; Reconstructive Procedures</strong> &ndash; Enhancing aesthetics and restoring function.</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743413453_side-1.jpg', 1, NULL, 0),
(465, 10, 84, 'service', 'Chocolate Protect Ur heart', '<p>Good news for chocolate lovers! Dark chocolate, when consumed in moderation, can have heart-protective benefits due to its rich content of antioxidants, flavonoids, and essential minerals.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How Chocolate Benefits Heart Health:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>✔ Rich in Antioxidants &ndash; Contains flavonoids that help reduce inflammation and improve heart function.<br />\r\n✔ Lowers Blood Pressure &ndash; Helps relax blood vessels, promoting healthy circulation.<br />\r\n✔ Improves Cholesterol Levels &ndash; Increases good cholesterol (HDL) and reduces bad cholesterol (LDL).<br />\r\n✔ Reduces Risk of Heart Disease &ndash; Regular consumption of dark chocolate (at least 70% cocoa) is linked to a lower risk of cardiovascular diseases.</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743413673_blog-1-440x260.jpg', 1, NULL, 0),
(466, 10, 84, 'service', 'Calcium protect your bones', '<p>Your body needs calcium to&nbsp;keep your bones dense and strong. Low bone density can cause your bones to become brittle and fragile. These weak bones can break more easily, even without an obvious injury. Vitamin D helps your body absorb calcium</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743413794_blog-4-440x260.jpg', 1, NULL, 0),
