(470, 10, 88, 'blog', 'What Should You Keep in Mind Before Initiating Insulin', '<p>The American Diabetes Association (ADA) recommends initiation of basal insulin at&nbsp;10 units/day or 0.1&ndash;0.2 units/kg/day, adjusted by 10&ndash;15% or 2&ndash;4 units once or twice weekly&nbsp;to reach a target fasting plasma glucose (FPG) in patients whose A1C remains uncontrolled after &gt;3 months of triple combination therapy, whose A1C ...</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743414679_blog-10.jpg', 1, NULL, 0),
(471, 10, 88, 'blog', 'Bood Sugar Levels – What IsNormal?', '<p>Normal fasting blood sugar levels are generally considered to be&nbsp;below 100 mg/dL (5.6 mmol/L), while levels between 100 and 125 mg/dL (5.6 to 6.9 mmol/L) indicate prediabetes, and 126 mg/dL (7.0 mmol/L) or higher on two separate tests suggests diabetes.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743414736_blog-9.jpg', 1, NULL, 0),
