(536, 12, 7, 'features', 'Curvas Cap', '<p>The family is&nbsp;thought to have originated during the middle of the Miocene period (23.7 to 4.9 million years ago)&nbsp;and undergone an initial radiation (divergence) in southeast Asia, before dispersing to Europe, the Americas and Africa. Choughs and treepies are believed to be the most primitive members of the Corvidae.</p>', '', 'Read More', '1743422189_03 (1).jpg', 1, NULL, 0),
